This paper primarily focuses on anonymity and security in web browsing, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also introduces a new operating system architecture designed for anonymity, which falls under the category of operating systems (cs.OS). Additionally, the paper discusses cloud storage and virtual machines, which are relevant to distributed computing (cs.DC) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation and evaluation of the system, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
